      "writtenOn": "2018-01-25T19:00:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "FWIU this code intends to strip the gitRoot prefix from protoDir. Let\u0027s be more direct here and use strings.TrimPrefix\n\nnote, however, that this does not work correctly on case-insensitive OSes, such as Windows.\n\nthinking about this more... it looks \n\n  git ls-tree --full-name --name-only HEAD \u003cfilename\u003e\n\nwill get you exactly what you need and it will piggy-back on git\u0027s implementation of prefix stripping. Consider that instead of --show-top-level",
      "revId": "110e6a20a1b9f0128689534452afbdcb2dcff172",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
