      "writtenOn": "2018-01-25T19:00:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "this does not have the file name, only directory and I am not sure how to fix it correctly.\n\nThe file name is available in\n\n   (*schemaConverter) schema()\n\nfunction, but it is relative to an import path, but which one? There are multiple import paths that we pass and the list of paths depends on whether this Go or Python project. This is getting complicated.\n\nThere is a much simpler alternative to gitiles URL which works 99% of the time:\n\n q :\u003d fmt.Sprintf(\"%s file:%s\", messageName, fileName)\n fmt.Sprintf(\"https://cs.chromium.org/%s\", url.PathEscape(q))\n\nwhere file name can be computed in main.go, right after loading the descriptor:\n\n  \tfile, _, err :\u003d descutil.Resolve(desc, flags.messageName)\n        ...\n        file.GetName() is the file name\n\n\nfor example, the result would be\n\n https://cs.chromium.org/SOMAlertsEvent%20file:infra/appengine/sheriff-o-matic/som/model/gen/events.proto\n\nwhich takes the user not only to the file, but to the message definition itself, which is pretty cool. Also it means you don\u0027t have to deal with git. Sorry I didn\u0027t see earlier that retrieving file name will be hard. :(",
